In this section, we present numerical simulations for the geometric biomembrane model of Problem 3.1 using the fully discrete scheme (24), (23) for quadratics polynomials m 1⁄4 2. We do not employ the computational tools of Section 5 except for the twisted banana, which exhibits very large domain deformations. These tools are indispensable for linears m 1⁄4 1. The algorithm was coded in C using the adaptive finite element library ALBERTA [41,40]. The description of each simulation is included in the caption of the corresponding figure. In all simulations the volume and surface area are preserved to machine precision.
